	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I tested a few more games on my Supaboy, which are not playable on my FC-16 Go.  I tested the games using my SNES PowerPak, since most of my SNES carts are in storage.  Faceball 2000 is not playable on the FC-16 Go, but it plays perfectly on my Supaboy.  Any idea as to why the FC-16 Go is incompatible?  Faceball 2000 loads on the FC-16 Go, the initial credits screen displays, you can select 1 or 2 players, but it only shows a black screen when loading into a level.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
